0.04: Fix Timestamp Format + Database Migration (2025-01-12)
- CRITICAL FIX: Timestamps now integers (Math.floor) instead of floats with decimals
- Fixes parsing error: "FormatException: Invalid radix-10 number" in Flutter app
- All Date.now() calls now wrapped with Math.floor() to ensure integer timestamps
- Flutter database migration added: v1→v2 adds confidence column to existing databases
- This fixes "table heart_rate has no column named confidence" SQL error
- No app reinstall needed - migration runs automatically on first launch

0.03: BLE Fix + App Loader Compatibility (2025-01-12)
- FIXED: BLE transmission now uses Bluetooth.println() instead of NRF.send()
- Now sends data via proper Nordic UART Service (UUID 6e400002/6e400003)
- Live data streaming to Flutter app working
- Added debug logging every 10 readings
- Updated metadata.json for BangleApps App Loader compatibility
- Added data wildcard for CSV files in metadata
- Format: lib.js → "pulsewatch" (no extension) for proper require()

0.02: Added control interface
- App now appears in launcher menu
- View status (recording state, file count, storage used)
- View statistics (detailed info)
- Delete data manually (for testing)
- Toggle recording on/off
- Green dot widget indicator

0.01: Initial release
- Background heart rate monitoring
- Accelerometer data collection
- Automatic 5-minute interval saves (testing)
- Green dot widget indicator
- Silent operation - no user interaction needed
